CHOLERA, DIARRHEA AND DYSENTERY UPDATE (31): CUBA (GRANMA) PRISON INMATES
*************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 2 Aug 2013
Source: Cafe Fuerte [in Spanish, machine trans., summ., edited]
http://cafefuerte.com/cuba/noticias-de-cuba/sociedad/3055-tres-muertos-por-colera-en-prision-provincial-de-granma


Two inmates died last Sun 29 Jul 2013, at the Granma provincial jail, known as Las Mangas, and 7 remain in a severe state as a result of the cholera epidemic that has infected more than 30 inmates in that prison. 3 inmates have died of the disease since 26 Jul 2013.

Cholera continues to hit other provinces and localities along the country, after the appearance of the first outbreak of the epidemic in Manzanillo in Granma Province, in June 2012.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Since the initial outbreak of cholera in Cuba's eastern Granma Province 13 months ago, the infection has been reported in the provinces on the eastern end of the island nation as well as other areas including in the capital Havana in the west. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/7Vfd.]
